We recommended management to ensure that the requisites for the bidding of infrastructure contracts provided in Section 17.4 of the Revised IRR of RA 9184 such as the detailed engineering investigations, surveys and designs, for the project have been sufficiently carried out and duly approved to ensure that all the undertakings are economically and efficiently carried out to protect the interest of the government; and:

a. 	Require the Engineering Office key personnel to closely monitor the project implementation and ensure that the project is on schedule;

b. 	Ensure the strict observance of the construction period as stipulated in the Contract and Notice to Proceed and strictly adhere to prescribed rules and regulations regarding a delay in completion of infrastructure projects;

c. 	Act with dispatch in resolving the existing issue/problems that are currently hampering/delaying the implementation and/or completion of projects.

We recommended that the management consider the following courses of action to improve the efficiency of project implementation:

Direct the concerned implementing offices to address the issues/ concerns that caused the non-implementation and/or delay in the completion of projects;



